<h3>how to design next FTA policy?</h3>
<ol>
<li>identify countries and regions that not only have the potential as a market for domestic goods and services but also have the scope to<em><strong> <span style="color:#3498db">enhance domestic competitiveness,</span></strong></em> especially in sectors covered under the PLI scheme.</li>
<li>Brexit advantage - FTA with UK + EU (BTIA) both</li>
<li>use of indian diaspora to leverage FTA&nbsp;</li>
<li>africa market</li></ol>
<h3>Conclusion</h3>
<p>The potential FTAs need to take cognisance of<span style="color:#3498db"> not only domestic strengths and global opportunities</span> but also the emerging geo-political landscape in the post-pandemic period.</p>
